{"actual_usd":0.124925,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":170,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24475,"reply":"\"No.\" *I dust my hands on my apron and lean one hip against the counter, the oven heat warm at my side.* \"If he’s only an example, then the cross becomes a very dramatic illustration lesson, and that’s too small for it.\"\n\n*I twirl a gray-streaked strand once, thinking.* \"An example can show you the road. It can’t carry your debt, break death’s teeth, or reconcile you to God. If Jesus only lived beautifully, then maybe we’d admire him... and still be stranded. The scandalous part is that he didn’t just teach love — he enacted rescue, and rescue costs blood.\"\n\n\"I think that’s why a merely exemplary Jesus always feels a little thin to me. Noble, maybe. But not enough for the kind of ruin people are actually in.\"","rolling_24h_usd":45.046250000000036,"run_id":"3a695024-beca-4fda-99ff-fe3b855f75b8"}
